FBIS3-14765 "drsov039_u_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-039 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Feb 1994 Latvia Three Russian Servicemen Attacked in Riga LD2502211294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 2024 GMT 25 Feb 94 LD2502211294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Roman Zadunayskiy] [Text] Moscow, 25 Feb -- Three Russian Army servicemen were attacked in Riga today by unknown assailants and were taken to military hospital in a serious condition. An ITAR-TASS correspondent learned from military sources in the Latvian capital that the three servicemen on leave from the Riga garrison -- a sergeant and two privates -- were badly beaten up. Two of the servicemen have concussion and the one of the privates was stabbed in the abdomen. The command of the Russian troops in the Baltics has appealed to the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the republic to take measures to investigate the incident. Under Russian legislation, in this case the law-enforcement bodies of Latvia should launch criminal proceedings and carry out an investigation.
